<BYLINE>By GEORGE GEDDA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A group of Panamanian dissidents is planning to undertake a military operation against strongman <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> by the beginning of next week, an opposition leader said Monday. Ambassador <PERSON> Juan </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sosa </PERSON>, who has maintained his loyalty to ousted President <PERSON> Eric </PERSON> <PERSON> Arturo </PERSON> <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON>, told reporters the group is made up of very knowledgeable officers who have many friends in the Panamanian Defense Forces, or PDF. <PERSON> Sosa </PERSON> gave no details, but the group apparently is comprised of high-ranking defectors from the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION> who came to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> shortly after <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s crisis erupted two months ago with <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON>'s ouster. One is <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> Lt. Col. <PERSON> Augusto </PERSON> <PERSON> Villalaz </PERSON>, who has been living in exile in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> for the past five weeks. He claimed that he and other <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> pilots flew more than 90,000 pounds of weapons from <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> before he defected. <PERSON> Sosa </PERSON>, who has refused to relinquish the embassy to a replacement envoy appointed by the new government in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>, said the dissident group has set up a `` military command'' and has `` intimate knowledge'' of the Defense Forces. `` We are very confident that the military actions will have the help, the support of people within the PDF,'' <PERSON> Sosa </PERSON> said. `` This is an asset we never had before.'' A military coup attempt against <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> last month was put down quickly. Asked wh