<DATELINE>BOULDER, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An African gray parrot alerted her owner by calling out his name when a Teflon-coated pan caught fire, but died from the fumes after the fire was extinguished. A veterinarian said burning <PERSON> Teflon </PERSON> has been found to cause respiratory arrest in birds. <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Colorado </ORGANIZATION> student, said 7-year-old <PERSON> Coco </PERSON> died exactly one year after his mother, <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON> <PERSON> Givens </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Aurora </LOCATION>, gave him the bird as a birthday present. <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON>, 21, who shares a house with five other students in <LOCATION> Boulder </LOCATION>, said one roommate arrived home early Saturday and put a pot of water on the stove to make spaghetti. <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON> said the roommate went to his room and made a telephone call, then fell asleep while the water boiled away. <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON> said about 4:30 a.m. he heard Coco screeching in the living room, next to the kitchen, and then calling his name. He got up and found the kitchen was filled with smoke and the Teflon lining of the red-hot pot was aflame. <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON> said he put out the fire and aired out the room, then checked on <PERSON> Coco </PERSON> and found that the bird appeared to be all right. But several minutes later, he said, he found the bird on the floor of her cage. Coco was valued at $ 1,000, could whistle the theme from the movie `` The Good, the Bad and the Ugly,'' and had a life expectancy of more than 100 years. `` This is really tragic,'' <PERSON> Barnes </PERSON> said. `` I was going to put her into my will'' to provide for future care. Veterinarian <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Dernell </PERSON> said <PERSON> Coco </PERSON>'s death is typical of other bird deaths involving Teflon cookware. He said an <LOCATION> Illinois </LOC