l enable us, state by state, to leap to 9,600-baud delivery,'' he said. For newspapers with systems that need slower speeds, the delivery rate can be reduced, but he said `` the news will fly on <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> circuits at 9600.'' That increase in capacity will avoid crowding that can slow copy delivery just as a crowded highway can slow traffic. `` We are raising the speed limit from 55 mph to 440 mph and ... we're widening the AP interstate from four lanes to eight,'' <PERSON> Boccardi </PERSON> said. He said three successful test installations of the new AP electronic darkroom for large newspapers are in place in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Petersburg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION>. In June, <PERSON> Boccardi </PERSON> said, the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> will unveil a PC-based electronic darkroom for smaller newspapers. He also announced that the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> will be offering members a new picture transmitter for the handling of their own photos _ a small, portable system enabling a photographer to transmit photos from color or black and white negatives without making prints. The AP already has put that system into use in covering such events as the Winter Olympic Games and the <ORGANIZATION> NCAA </ORGANIZATION> basketball championships in March. The transmitter, called the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> @ <ORGANIZATION> Leafax </ORGANIZATION> 35, was developed to AP specifications by <ORGANIZATION> Leaf </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Natick </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass </LOCATION>. AP holds exclusive distribution rights. By the end of the year, <PERSON> Boccardi </PERSON> said, the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> will begin operating a new service called DataFeature Graphics that will deliver news graphics offered by syndicates and supplemental services. He also said the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> has now converted worldwide to all-color photography, a step taken in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> more than a year ago. By next spring, he said, a new financial markets system will be ready for <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> members. `` You will be able to use our feed to create stock tables in virtually any form you wish, emphasizing local companies or industries, for example,'' he said.
