here, I'm more than delighted to send them and my <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> personnel are ready to go,'' <PERSON> Yost </PERSON> told reporters. `` Really raring and ready to go.'' Administratively, the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> is part of the <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>, but by law, the agency also falls under <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> jurisdiction for national security purposes. <ORGANIZATION> Congressional </ORGANIZATION> sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> has offered to pay the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION>'s expenses in mounting the gulf patrols. The <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> has been hit hard by budget cuts that have resulted from deficit-reduction efforts. The service has a $ 2.7 billion budget this year, which <PERSON> Yost </PERSON> says is $ 100 million less than needed. As result, the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> in February closed almost 30 stations and offices, cut anti-drug patrols, and halted routine rescue patrols. The administration last month came up with a plan to shift money within the <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> and permit more anti-drug patrols. That proposal has yet to be approved by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. The `` Island'' class boats that would be used in the gulf operations have a maximum speed of more than 26 knots and carry a crew of 16, according to <PERSON> Sandifer </PERSON>. The vessels are armed with one 20mm machine gun in the front, and two 7.62 mm machine guns elsewhere Another 20mm machine gun can be added. Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Ohio </LOCATION>, a member of the <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, said, `` Those boats could be good, but they do n't have any of their own defense against missiles and that's what our ships are running into these days in the gulf.'' `` I'm willing to look at the proposal, but as of right now, it does n't make a lot of sense,'' said <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON>. `` I hate to see us pull the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> off drug work.'' Last fall, the Pentagon considered sending <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> vessels to the gulf, but decided against the idea, in part because the boats are so lightly armed. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> has attacked shipping with a variety of boats, particularly speedboats. The Iranians have at least two dozen Swedish-made `` Boghammer'' boats, which have been armed with machine guns and rocket launchers.
