. <PERSON> Sapphire </PERSON> is a subsidiary of <PERSON> Carlin </PERSON>. A similar decision by another federal appeals court previously enabled <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> to rid its 976 networks of dial-a-porn services in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>.
