 _ Elsewhere in television: RECORD 11 TOP 10s FOR ` 60 MINUTES' _ CBS' newsmagazine `` 60 Minutes'' has set a record by placing in the top 10 in the Nielsen prime-time network ratings for the 11th season in a row. Only `` Gunsmoke,'' with 13, has more top-10 finishes, unless you count all the <PERSON> Lucille </PERSON> <PERSON> Ball </PERSON> vehicles combined: `` I Love <PERSON> Lucy </PERSON>,'' `` The Lucy Show'' and `` Here's <PERSON> Lucy </PERSON>,'' combined racked up 15 top 10s, 10 of them in a row. `` 60 Minutes'' just finished its 20th season and ranked eighth out of 105 regularly scheduled network programs. HIT SHOWS _ The hottest comedies in syndication are `` Family Ties'' and `` Cheers,'' according to <PERSON> Lucille </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Salhany </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> Domestic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Division </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION>. The two shows were tops in both total households and key demographics, ending the long reign of `` M-A-S-H.'' `` Cheers'' was most popular with men, 18-49, and `` Family Ties'' with women, 18-49
