<TEXT>
 `` Adventures in Babysitting'' -LRB- Touchstone Home Video; VHS @ Beta, $ 89.95; Rated PG-13 `` Adventures in Babysitting'' is another adventure-comedy for the teen set from the <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Touchstone </ORGANIZATION> factory. <PERSON> Elisabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Shue </PERSON> -LRB- `` Karate Kid'' -RRB- stars as <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> <PERSON> Parker </PERSON>, a high school senior in a <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> suburb who reluctantly agrees to babysit for a neighbor's kids after her boyfriend stands her up. Then her best friend calls in panic from the downtown bus station _ she has run away from home, run out of money and begs <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> to come get her. So <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> and her three charges head down the expressway, where they promptly get a flat tire, discover <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> has forgotten her purse, fall in with a good-natured but impulsive tow truck driver and get led into a series of ever-more unlikely predicaments, mostly involving a sinister gang of auto thieves. The movie starts off promisingly, with a nice feel for the middle-class suburban milieu and a disarming spontaneity that makes you eager to see what weird thing will happen next. But as the complications grow, screenwriter <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Simkins </PERSON> begins relying too much on stock situations, such as car chases and people hanging from 40th-story windows. Before it all ends, with everyone safely tucked into bed, <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> discovers that her boyfriend is a two-timing louse and has already started a new romance with a kind-hearted college kid. Miss <PERSON> Shue </PERSON>, a lovely and spirited young actress, comes through it all remarkably well, and the kids are n't bad either. A fair amount of raunchy language explains the PG-13 rating. _ By <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Silverman </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Wri