<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>Star Watch: Demi Moore Graduates From Brat Pack</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB THOMAS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Once a reluctant member of the much-maligned Brat Pack, <PERSON> Demi </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> has graduated to become a star in her own right, a budding producer, wife of <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> of TV's `` Moonlighting'' fame and a future mother These dizzying changes have somehow left the actress more serene than ever. During a recent interview at <ORGANIZATION> Tri-Star </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION>, where she occupies offices for development of screen projects, she seemed calm and controlled, a 25-year-old confident of the future. <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> currently stars in `` The Seventh Sign'' as a pregnant wife who is the central figure in a present-day threat of a biblical apocalypse. The film has received a cool response from reviewers and the public. `` A lot of people have commented that it might be in that genre of films such as ` <PERSON> Rosemary </PERSON>'s Baby' and ` The Omen,''' she said. `` I do n't think we set out for it to be that type of film. When I read the script, the story always had an uplifting message, whereas those other films always dealt with the devil and the concept of an outside, evil force coming in and taking over. `` For me the only evil force in the movie is the human race and what we're doing to ourselves. `` It's the first time I've had to carry a movie, and on that level it was more challenging,'' she said. `` Also, it's a different character, and the subject matter was much weightier. I've always been associated with light, romantic comedies.'' <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> said some of her roles, in such movies as `` About Last Night'' and `` St. Elmo's Fire'' had `` moments of emotional depth that had to be reached. Particularly, ` About Last Night' exposed that I was capable of more than just a frivolous, looking-good -LRB- character -RRB-.'' Tri-Star thought so, and she is now developing a film project based on a book she discovered. `` You just ca n't be at the studios' mercy to bring you that ideal role,'' she said <PERSON> Moore </PERSON>, whose parents spotted the name <PERSON> Demi </PERSON> in a fashion magazine, had an unsettled childhood. She attended 30 different schools as her advertising manager father moved to various newspapers of a large chain. Her childhood curiously parallels those of other young stars such as <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Cruise </PERSON> and <PERSON> Rebecca </PERSON> <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Mornay </PERSON>. `` That experience definitely has something to do with how I ended up here,'' <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> said. `` When you move around a lot, you're always having to adjust and fit in, meet people and situations `` I've talked to a number of people who have had similar experiences, <PERSON> Rebecca </PERSON> being one. I do n't quite know what it is. Maybe it's just being able to adjust, fit in, cope, create whatever you need to survive, make it work. `` There are two choices: You can become introverted, isolated and alone; or you can become extroverted and put yourself out there and try to fit into the group so you're not alone. I do n't think that always leaves you with a great sense of yourself or of security.'' <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> chose to be extroverted, and at 16 she dropped out of school to become a model. She had the flawless beauty, but at 5 feet-5 -LCB- inches, not the height. So she took acting classes and at 18 landed the role of <PERSON> Jackie </PERSON> <PERSON> Templeton </PERSON> on the TV soap `` General Hospital.'' Her first major film role was in `` Blame It on <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION>,'' in which she appeared topless as <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Caine </PERSON>'s headstrong daughter. More films followed: `` No Small Affair,'' `` St. Elmo's Fire,'' `` One Crazy Summer,'' `` Wisdom.'' In the latter, she co-starred with <PERSON> Emilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Estevez </PERSON>, who was then her fiance. Last Nov. 21 she married <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nev. </LOCATION>. She said their baby is due in late summer <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> was well prepared for her pregnancy. To research `` The Seventh Sign,'' she talked to pregnant women and obstetricians and visited delivery rooms. `` It was a lot of fun for me,'' she said. `` I had a leotard suit with a belly that weighed 10 to 15 pounds. I wore it for two weeks before the film started, to get the feeling, the walk. People responded to me differently. `` I also had a prosthetic device which was sculpted of rubber and took six hours to apply, gluing it to my skin. Thank God I only had to wear it four or five times. `` For me it is much more exciting that I got to play pregnant and make it so realistic, and now to have the real thing happen.''
</TEXT>
