<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>The Artists: Soprano Worked Overtime As Met Season Wound Down</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MIKE SILVERMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 She's a bird! She's a maid! She's a flirtatious landowner! She's a kid sister! She's <PERSON> Dawn </PERSON> <PERSON> Upshaw </PERSON>, supersoprano, and during the final weeks of the Metropolitan Opera season, her sweet, lyric voice seemed to be piping up all over the place. `` If anybody had told me I was going to be doing what I did this season, I'd have been flabbergasted,'' Miss <PERSON> Upshaw </PERSON> said in a recent interview. `` It was very draining.'' What she did, within the space of two months, was sing the off-stage role of the <LOCATION> Forest </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bird </LOCATION> in <PERSON> Wagner </PERSON>'s `` Siegfried''; the comic housemaid <PERSON> Despina </PERSON> in <PERSON> Mozart </PERSON>'s `` Cosi Fan Tutte''; <PERSON> Adina </PERSON>, the heroine of <PERSON> Donizetti </PERSON>'s `` The Elixir of Love''; and <PERSON> Sophie </PERSON>, the younger sister of <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION> in <PERSON> Massenet </PERSON>'s `` Werther.'' `` It's not something I would want to do very often _ so many different things all at once,'' she said. `` The preparation was not the problem; it was more concentration.'' The centerpiece of all this activity was four performances as <PERSON> Adina </PERSON>, by far the biggest role the 27-year-old soprano has sung at the Met, and one she almost did n't sing at all. `` I was the cover -LRB- understudy -RRB- for <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Battle </PERSON>, and supposed to be singing the smaller role of <LOCATION> Giannetta </LOCATION>,'' she said. `` The night of the first performance I was on my way out the door at 10 to 7 when I got the call saying <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> was sick and could I please go on as <PERSON> Adina </PERSON>.'' The same question had been put to her last fall when illness forced <PERSON> Judith </PERSON> <PERSON> Blegen </PERSON> to cancel a run of <LOCATION> Adinas </LOCATION>. `` They gave me a choice of going on, but it was a new role, a new style for me,'' she sai