<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> Seoul </LOCATION> metropolitan government has established a Home-Stay Program involving 668 Korean families to cater to foreign tourists expected for the Olympic Games in September. Part of the preparation for the host homes involves learning Western-style cooking. `` The basic price of the Home-Stay Program -LRB- $ 25 a person per night -RRB- includes breakfast and, obviously, most Western visitors will not be used to the Korean-style morning meal of soup, fish, rice and kimchi -LRB- a spicy cabbage dish -RRB-,'' said a city government official. `` We want to be able to offer them the kind of breakfast dishes they are used to at home. That's no problem in our city's hotels _ but perhaps a new cooking experience for some Korean housewives.'' The homes in the program, which is operated by the <ORGANIZATION> Korea </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Travel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION>, include traditional Korean-style houses and modern apartments.
