rnatives to the acquisition of USG, including an attempt to elect nominees to <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors at the annual meeting next month <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> sued <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> late last year, claiming that the partnership violated federal securities law in its negotiations with USG.
