<TEXT>
 The stock market gained ground today amid expectations of further signs of a healthy economic outlook. The government is due to issue its estimate Tuesday of the economic growth rate for the first quarter of the year. Advance estimates on Wall Street call for the figure on inflation-adjusted growth of the gross national product to come in somewhere between 2 percent and 2 -LCB- percent at an annual rate. Wall Streeters also are looking for a solid increase in the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s index of leading economic indicators for March, scheduled to be reported on Friday. While the expected data would be positive for corporate earnings prospects, brokers say they could also put upward pressure on interest rates. Thus, they say, it is a tough call how the stock market will respond to the news.
