<HEAD>Show Promoter Buys Vegas Resort</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ROBERT MACY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Massachusetts-based trade show company is acquiring the <ORGANIZATION> Sands </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hotel </ORGANIZATION> and Casino, a 36-year fixture on the <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> strip, for $ 110 million, the company announced Monday. Interface Group is acquiring the Sands, a 36-year fixture on the <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, from <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which is owned by financier <PERSON> Kirk </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>. The purchase includes the resort-casino and 60 acres of land on the Strip. <PERSON> Sheldon </PERSON> <PERSON> Adelson </PERSON>, Interface's chairman, called the Sands purchase a natural extension of the Interface operations, which already include trade shows, a New England-based travel operation and a small airline. <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> will continue operating the hotel until the five Interface partners obtain a <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> gaming license, which could take six months to a year, <PERSON> Adelson </PERSON> said. Once licensing is completed, Interface plans to build a 1,000-room tower that could cost $ 60 million to $ 70 million, <PERSON> Adelson </PERSON> said. The company, based in <LOCATION> Needham </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, also may build major convention facilities on acreage purchased at the rear of the 750-room hotel and casino, which is located in the heart of the rapidly-growing Strip. <PERSON> Adelson </PERSON> said <PERSON> Henri </PERSON> <PERSON> Lewin </PERSON>, former president of the <ORGANIZATION> Las </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Vegas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hilton </ORGANIZATION>, would take over management of the hotel. <PERSON> Lewin </PERSON> is chairman of Aristocrat Hotels of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>, a hotel management and consulting firm. <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> purchased the Sands and the Desert Inn in February from the <ORGANIZATION> Summa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corporation </ORGANIZATION> for $ 167 million. <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> will retain ownership of the Desert Inn. Interface produces the COMDEX computer industry show, the city's second-largest, attracting nearly 100,000 delegates annually Interface also promotes a housewares show and a film festival in the city, as well as computer industry shows throughout the world. `` We plan to integrate our travel and trade show division vertically, so that the Sands and other <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> hotels are included in our tour packages,'' <PERSON> Adelson </PERSON> said. `` We are considering basing one of our aircraft in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> to service this market.'' The Interface travel division is the largest tour operator in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> and operates four L-1011 jet aircraft under its Five Star Airline division.
